    The function list displays all the @{"Functions" link FUNCTION} you have created.

    Here are some of the shortcuts for controlling this list:-

        DoubleClick         = Open/Close Function.
        Shift + Doubleclick = Toggle Enable/Disable.
        Space               = Toggle Enable/Disable.
        Alt + Up            = Move Function Up The List.
        Alt + Down          = Move Function Down The List.

    @{FG shine}New Function:@{FG text}

    Create a new @{"Function" link FUNCTION}.

    @{FG shine}Add Method:@{FG text}

    Add a new @{"Method" link METHOD} to the active function.

    @{FG shine}Duplicate:@{FG text}

    Duplicate a @{"function" link FUNCTION}/@{"method" link METHOD}.

    @{FG shine}Delete:@{FG text}

    Delete a @{"Function" link FUNCTION} or @{"Method" link METHOD}.

    @{FG shine}Analyse Function:@{FG text}

    Analyse the active @{"function" link FUNCTION}.

    @{FG shine}View Analysis:@{FG text}

    Open the @{"Analysis Window" link ANALYSISWINDOW}.

    @{FG shine}Function/Method Preferences:@{FG text}

    This is the display area set aside for @{"Function" link FUNCTION} and @{"Method" link METHOD} preferences.

    @{FG shine}Save:@{FG text}

    Save changes to disk.

    @{FG shine}Use:@{FG text}

    Save changes for current session.

    @{FG shine}Cancel:@{FG text}

    Discard changes.

@endnode

