@node ANALYSISWINDOW "Analysis Window"

    This section allows you to find out how successful a function would have
    been in predicting previous lottery draws. By using this facility you
    should be able to detect possible patterns emerging in the functions you
    have created.

    @{b}Report:@{ub}

    This section shows miscellaneous data about the selected function.

    @{FG shine}Standard:@{FG text}

    The number of times each standard combination was predicted.

    @{FG shine}Bonus:@{FG text}

    The number of times each bonus combination was predicted.

    @{FG shine}Total:@{FG text}

    The total number of times each combination was predicted.

    @{FG shine}Last Picked:@{FG text}

    The last date each combination appeared.

    @{FG shine}Frequency:@{FG text}

    The average, minumum or maximum number of draws between appearances.

    @{FG shine}Next Due:@{FG text}

    The probable date of the next appearance. Note that this is only an
    approximate date based on the frequency of each combination, and should
    be used with the graph (below) to give you a better idea of whether an
    appearance is likely.

    @{FG shine}Show Frequency As:@{FG text}

    Display frequency as average, minimum or maximum gap between wins.

    @{b}Graph:@{ub}

    This is a graphical view of the above report.

    @{FG shine}Filter:@{FG text}

    Filter out certain results to get a clearer view of what you need.

    @{FG shine}Zoom:@{FG text}

    Zoom in/out of the graph.

@endnode

@node FUNCTION "Function"

        Functions act as controllers for all the methods attached to them.
    The function sends the lottery results to each @{"method" link METHOD} in turn. Each of
    the methods then analyses the results and increases the value of the
    numbers it has chosen. The way it does this depends on the method
    itself. See each method's online help for more details, which can be
    viewed via the method preferences.

        When all the methods have been processed, the function chooses the
    best selection possible according to each numbers total return value.
    If the function needs to choose from numbers with an equal value, the
    option Favour Hot Numbers will be the deciding factor. If set, it will
    choose the most recent of these numbers, otherwise it will select the
    numbers that haven`t been drawn for the longest time.

        See @{"How It Works" link HOWITWORKS} for more details.

    @{b}Function Preferences:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Include Bonus in Prediction:@{FG text}

    Include Bonus numbers when processing results.

    @{FG shine}Favour Hot Numbers:@{FG text}

    If there are too many numbers of equal value in the prediction table,
    this option will decide whether the function picks the most recently
    drawn numbers, or the numbers that have not been drawn for longest.

    @{FG shine}Results processing limit:@{FG text}

    Here you can set the function to limit the results sent to each method.

    e.g. Setting this to 100 will only send the most recent 100 draws to
         each @{"method" link METHOD}. If there is less than 100 draws in the database this
         setting will have no effect.

    @{FG shine}Repeat draw ball limit:@{FG text}

    Set this for how many numbers you want to allow to be repeated from
    the most recent lottery draw.

    @{FG shine}Sequential draw ball limit:@{FG text}

    Set this for how many pairs of sequential numbers are allowed be picked.

    e.g 26, 27          ... one pair
        26, 27, 28      ... two pairs
        26, 27, 29, 30  ... two pairs

@endnode

@node METHOD "Method"

        A method is a way of predicting a set of numbers. It analyses the
    results data passed by the controlling @{"Function" link FUNCTION} and chooses a selection
    of numbers it expects to appear in the lottery.

        Each method has its own individual preferences which can be tailored
    to suit your needs. Set them the way you believe it can correctly
    generate a positive result for you.

        The preferences vary from method to method so details cannot be given
    here, but online help is available for each method.

    @{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub}

        Please take note that some methods require that lottery draws are
    entered into the database in the order they were drawn.

@endnode

@node FORTUNESETTINGS "Fortune Settings"

    @{"   " link FORTUNESETTINGSMENU} Menu

    @{b}Results:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Columns:@{FG text}

    This is to select the columns you want displayed in the results database.
    Choose Status, Position, Style and Pen. Status can be toggled by a doubleclick.

    @{FG shine}Sort Draw:@{FG text}

    Sort draw in ascending order or the order in which it was entered.

    @{FG shine}Date Format:@{FG text}

    Choose the format of the date.

    @{FG shine}Separator Bars:@{FG text}

    Separate columns with a vertical bar.

    @{FG shine}Show Day With Date:@{FG text}

    Show the day in the date column.

    @{FG shine}Include Bonus in Total:@{FG text}

    Calculate the Draw Total including or excluding the value of the Bonus Ball(s).

    @{b}Prediction:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Standard Gauge:@{FG text}

    Set colour of standard gauge.

    @{FG shine}Border:@{FG text}

    Set the style of the standard gauge border.

    @{FG shine}Ball Pen:@{FG text}

    Set the highlight pen for standard balls.

    @{FG shine}Value Pen:@{FG text}

    Set the highlight pen for standard values.

    @{FG shine}Selected Gauge:@{FG text}

    Set colour of selected gauge.

    @{FG shine}Border:@{FG text}

    Set the style of the selected gauge border.

    @{FG shine}Ball Pen:@{FG text}

    Set the highlight pen for selected balls.

    @{FG shine}Value Pen:@{FG text}

    Set the highlight pen for selected values.

    @{FG shine}Sort Predictions:@{FG text}

    Sort predictions in priority order or ascending order.
    This option only affects the prediction that is shown on the main window.

    @{b}Analysis:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Analysis Limit:@{FG text}

    Set a limit for the number of recent results you want analysed. There are now
    three modes available to you: Short, Medium & Long. Set them accordingly.

    @{FG shine}Column Width:@{FG text}

    Set the width of the columns drawn on the analysis graph.

    @{FG shine}Column Spacing:@{FG text}

    Set the spacing between columns on the analysis graph.

    @{FG shine}Date Format:@{FG text}

    Choose the format of the date shown on the analysis.

    @{FG shine}Display Gauge:@{FG text}

    Draw a gauge on the analysis graph.

    @{FG shine}Display Scale:@{FG text}

    Draw scale marker lines on the analysis graph.

    @{FG shine}Display Day:@{FG text}

    Show the day with any dates on the analysis report.

    @{FG shine}Gauge Colour:@{FG text}

    Set the colour(s) of the gauge.

    @{FG shine}Standard Colour:@{FG text}

    Set the colour(s) of the standard result columns.

    @{FG shine}Bonus Colour:@{FG text}

    Set the colour(s) of the bonus result columns.

    @{b}Misc 1:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Confirm Quit:@{FG text}

    Ask for confirmation via a requester when exiting program.

    @{FG shine}Confirm Overwrite:@{FG text}

    Ask for confirmation when overwriting an existing data file.

    @{FG shine}Confirm Delete:@{FG text}

    Ask for confirmation when deleting results data and functions/methods.

    @{FG shine}Save Data On Exit:@{FG text}

    Save current data when exiting program.

    @{FG shine}Save Prefs On Exit:@{FG text}

    Save current prefs when exiting program.

    @{FG shine}Save Functions On Exit:@{FG text}

    Save current functions when exiting program.

    @{FG shine}Save Format On Exit:@{FG text}

    Save current format when exiting program.

    @{b}Misc 2:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Open Function Tree:@{FG text}

    Open all branches of the function tree when loading function data.

    @{FG shine}Create Icons:@{FG text}

    Create icons when saving data files.

    @{FG shine}Save Format With Data:@{FG text}

    Save format in any data files. When loading data files with format data
    the format settings are always updated. This option is useful if you take
    part in more than one lottery and each has a different format.

    @{FG shine}Flush Methods On Exit:@{FG text}

    Remove all methods from memory when exiting program.

    @{FG shine}Disable Progress Display:@{FG text}

    Prevent the progress window opening when performing operations. Setting
    this can speed up operations quite considerably.

    @{FG shine}Create Backups:@{FG text}

    Backup data files before saving.

    @{FG shine}Disable Multiselect:@{FG text}

    Disable multiselect on the results database.

    @{FG shine}Link Predictions:@{FG text}

    Link the basic prediction to the full prediction listing so they both show
    the same prediction.

    @{FG shine}Save:@{FG text}

    Save changes to disk.

    @{FG shine}Use:@{FG text}

    Save changes for current session.

    @{FG shine}Cancel:@{FG text}

    Discard changes.

@endnode

@node FORTUNESETTINGSMENU "Fortune Settings Menu"

    @{b}Project --+@{ub}
              @{b}| - Open...           O@{ub}    @{i}Open a new fortune prefs file.@{ui}
              @{b}| - -------------------@{ub}
              @{b}| - Save As...        A@{ub}    @{i}Save fortune prefs under a new name.@{ui}
    @{b}Edit -----+@{ub}
              @{b}| - Reset To Defaults D@{ub}    @{i}Reset to default prefs.@{ui}
              @{b}| - Last Saved        L@{ub}    @{i}Reload last saved fortune prefs.@{ui}
              @{b}| - Restore           R@{ub}    @{i}Restore prefs for current session.@{ui}

@endnode

@node FORMATSETTINGS "Format Settings"

    @{"   " link FORMATSETTINGSMENU} Menu

    @{b}Format:@{ub}

    @{FG shine}Draw Balls:@{FG text}

    Set the number of balls drawn in the lottery (not including bonus).

    @{FG shine}Bonus Balls:@{FG text}

    Set the number of bonus balls drawn in the lottery.

    @{FG shine}Highest Number:@{FG text}

    Set the highest number ball drawn in the lottery.

    @{FG shine}No. of Predictions:@{FG text}

    Set the number of selections you require to play the lottery.

    @{b}Dates:@{ub}

    This section allows the edit window to set the date for you automatically,
    when adding new entries to the results database. If no date settings have
    been entered, the date will be set to the current date.

    You are required to set a start date for each day a draw takes place.
    It may be that the lottery company has stopped draws on certain days in
    which case you will have to set a finish date. I have not yet heard of
    draws being stopped, but the option is there if you need it.

    @{FG shine}Dates:@{FG text}

    This list shows start and finish dates of the lottery.

    @{FG shine}Add:@{FG text}

    Add a new date setting to the list.

    @{FG shine}Delete:@{FG text}

    Delete a date setting from the list.

    @{FG shine}From:@{FG text}

    The From option is always active.

    @{FG shine}From Date:@{FG text}

    Set the date that a lottery draw was started.

    @{FG shine}To:@{FG text}

    Select this to stop the date setting being used after the To date is reached.

    @{FG shine}To Date:@{FG text}

    Set the date that a lottery draw ended.

    @{FG shine}Frequency:@{FG text}

    How often does this particular draw take place.

    @{FG shine}Save:@{FG text}

    Save changes to disk.

    @{FG shine}Use:@{FG text}

    Save changes for current session.

    @{FG shine}Cancel:@{FG text}

    Discard changes.

@endnode

@node FORMATSETTINGSMENU "Format Settings Menu"

    @{b}Project --+@{ub}
              @{b}| - Open...           O@{ub}    @{i}Open a new format prefs file.@{ui}
              @{b}| - -------------------@{ub}
              @{b}| - Save As...        A@{ub}    @{i}Save format prefs under a new name.@{ui}
    @{b}Edit -----+@{ub}
              @{b}| - Reset To Defaults D@{ub}    @{i}Reset to default prefs.@{ui}
              @{b}| - Last Saved        L@{ub}    @{i}Reload last saved format prefs.@{ui}
              @{b}| - Restore           R@{ub}    @{i}Restore prefs for current session.@{ui}

@endnode

@node AUTHOR "Author"

    If you need to contact me with questions, bug reports, suggestions or
    anything else you can send e-mail to:

        @{b}lottery@cableinet.co.uk@{ub}

    If you don't have e-mail access you can send letters to:

        @{b}Jon Close
        35 Belfast Road
        Liverpool
        Merseyside L13 5SR
        ENGLAND@{ub}

    Wherever possible, please send e-mail for a quick reply.

    @{b}--- Questions, Suggestions, etc. ------------------------------------------@{ub}

    I will try to answer all mail, but due to a severe lack of time I may only
    be able to answer those that need a reply.

    @{b}--- Bug Reports -----------------------------------------------------------@{ub}

    Please make bug reports as detailed as possible. Include enforcer report,
    snoopdos log, etc, if available. If I can't reproduce the bug it's unlikely
    that I'll be able to fix it.

@endnode

@node MUI "MUI"

                          This application uses

                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1992-97 by Stefan Stuntz

    MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces. With
    the  aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application has the
    ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

    MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package containing
    lots of examples and more information about registration please look for
    a  file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest version number) on
    your local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send

                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

                                  to

                             Stefan Stuntz
                        Eduard-Spranger-Straße 7
                             80935 München
                                GERMANY

             Support and online registration is available at

                          http://www.sasg.com/

@endnode

@node HISTORY "History"

    @{b}Date         Version    Information@{ub}

    01-Aug-98    1.0        First public release.

    10-Aug-98    1.1        Added support for multiple bonus balls.
                            @{i}(requested by Garry Simmonds)@{ui}

                            Fixed printing of results without a bonus ball.
                            Unless the bonus column was disabled in Fortune
                            settings, a bonus column would always be printed.

                            Fixed calculation of analysis frequency.

    10-Oct-98    1.2        Added a separate processing limit to High&Low method.

                            Fixed error that was introduced with multiple bonus balls.
                            Memory was trashed if draws were to be sorted in ascending
                            order and the number of bonus balls was set to 0.
                            @{i}(reported by Ken Waugh)@{ui}

                            The FORTUNE: assign is no longer needed. Fortune now
                            searches the program directory for all necessary files.

                            Fixed a problem with some resources not being freed on exit.

                            Improved installation script.

                            Analysis frequency can now be shown as average, minimum or
                            maximum gap between wins.

                            Six enhanced methods are now available for registered users.

                            Added "Draw Order" method allowing selection of numbers in
                            the order they have been recently drawn. An enhanced version
                            is available to registered users.

                            Added "Analysis Mode" for Short, Medium & Long analysis.

                            A full prediction list is now available showing each ball
                            in order of its probability of being selected.

                            Fortune now uses NList to display results/predictions.
                            (NList.mcc © 1996-98 Gilles Masson)

                            Results sorting is now controlled by NList.

                            Sort Predictions option moved from Format settings to
                            global Fortune settings.

@endnode                    


